The ANC in Parliament has postponed its caucus lekgotla in order to give its members time to pay their respects to Winnie Madikizela-Mandela. Madikizela-Mandela died on Monday following a long illness. The lekgotla was scheduled to take place from 13 to 16 April but has now been rescheduled to take place from 20 to 23 April. National Assembly Chief Whip Jackson Mthembu will on Wednesday lead the caucus delegation to Mama Winnie’s house in Soweto where they will offer their condolences. Madikizela-Mandela will be buried on Saturday 14  April in Johannesburg. -TNA Reporter